Closed Thanksgiving


						The Makerspace Digital Fab and Machine Shop will be closed 11/24 and 11/25 for Thanksgiving. Student Orgs will continue to have access.
					














            Current
          Heading link



 
Copy link



Use our online job submission form: Project Submission
 
For the safety of our staff and users we have implemented the following changes to Makerspace procedures:
 

Do not come to the Makerspace to submit files – use our online job submission form: Project Submission
We may have unexpected closures or production delays if staff need to quarantine.
Please do not come to the Makerspace if you feel unwell, are coughing, or have a fever.
Please see our updated hours









            Intro
          Heading link



 
Copy link



The Makerspace has equipment and services to support all members of the UIC College of Engineering in prototyping and manufacturing for classwork, research, and student organizations. We also support Engineering research projects.








            UIC Makerspace Face Shield
          Heading link



 
Copy link



Designs and instructions to make the UIC Makerspace Face Shield: https://github.com/UIC-Makerspace/FaceShield








            Accommodations
          Heading link



 
Copy link



If you require accommodations, or have any apprehensions about using the Makerspace, we are here to help! Please email us and we will work with you to find or create accommodations that best suit your needs.















 























